HEADWORD: Seaboard
<hw>Sea"board`</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Bordering upon, or being near,
the sea; seaside; seacoast; <as>as, a <ex>seaboard</ex>
town</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

